# Sailing Yachts Specs Database

## Project Overview
A searchable, filterable web application showcasing a comprehensive database of sailing yacht specifications. Deployed on Vercel using a Next.js frontend with a PostgreSQL backend.

**Target Users**: Sailing enthusiasts, boat buyers, marine researchers
**Key Value**: Easy comparison of yacht specs across manufacturers and models

---

## Goals & Acceptance Criteria

### MVP (Minimum Viable Product)
- [ ] Responsive web app deployed on Vercel
- [ ] List view of yachts with core specs + dynamic spec categories
- [ ] Filter by: length range, manufacturer, rig type, keel type, AND any new spec categories added later (auto-generated)
- [ ] Sort by: length, displacement, year, and any other numeric specs
- [ ] Detail page for each yacht with full specifications, images, and customer sentiment (if available)
- [ ] Compare feature: select 2-3 yachts to view side-by-side (auto-adapts to common spec fields)
- [ ] Search functionality (text search on model name, manufacturer, and spec values)
- [ ] Seed database with 4-5 yachts per size category (small/medium/large) → ~12-15 total, scraped from manufacturer sites
- [ ] Responsive design: clean, minimalist, elegant (inspired by top sailing yacht websites)
- [ ] Basic SEO (meta tags, structured data)
- [ ] Admin interface: CRUD for yachts/manufacturers/specs, plus ability to add custom button/link per boat

### Stretch Goals (post-MVP)
- Brokerage listings and price tracking
- User accounts and saved comparisons
- Community submissions with moderation
- Advanced metrics (sail area ratios, PHRF, comfort ratio)
- Export to PDF/CSV
- Bulk import via CSV

---

## Architecture

### High-Level Diagram
```
┌─────────────────┐
│   Vercel CDN    │  ← Static assets, images
└────────┬────────┘
         │
┌────────▼────────┐
│  Next.js 14     │  ← App Router, React, TypeScript
│  (Serverless)   │  ← Route Handlers (API)
└────────┬────────┘
         │
┌────────▼────────┐
│   PostgreSQL    │  ← Supabase/Neon DB
│   (Drizzle ORM) │  ← Type-safe queries
└─────────────────┘
```

### Why This Stack?
- **Next.js**: Best-in-class Vercel integration, SSG/SSR flexibility, API routes
- **TypeScript**: Type safety for complex spec schemas, catches errors early
- **PostgreSQL**: Relational data fits yacht models + manufacturers + specs perfectly
- **Drizzle**: Modern TypeScript-first ORM, minimal abstraction, works on edge runtime
- **Tailwind CSS**: Rapid UI development, consistent design system
- **shadcn/ui**: Pre-built accessible components (datatable, dialogs, forms)

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Rationale |
|-------|------------|-----------|
| Framework | Next.js 14 (App Router) | Vercel-native, React 19, Server Components |
| Language | TypeScript 5 | Type safety, better DX |
| Database | PostgreSQL (Supabase/Neon) | Free tier, managed, reliable |
| ORM | Drizzle | Type-safe,kitchen-sink schema support |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS | Utility-first, fast iteration |
| Components | shadcn/ui | Radix UI primitives, customizable |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Zod | Validation, performance |
| Images | Next.js Image + Vercel Blob | Optimization, CDN |
| Testing | Vitest + Testing Library | Fast unit tests |
| Linting | ESLint + Prettier | Code quality |
| Deployment | Vercel | Automatic previews, edge functions |

