## Data Acquisition: Scraping Strategy

### Size Categories & Target Manufacturers

We'll seed **4-5 yachts per size category** (avoiding HanseYachts AG brands: Hanse, Sealine, Dehler, Fjord, Ryck, Moody).

| Category | Length Range | Target Manufacturers (examples) |
|----------|--------------|--------------------------------|
| Small | < 10m (33 ft) | Catalina, Hunter, J/Boats, West Wight Potter, San Juan, Pearson |
| Medium | 10-14m (33-46 ft) | Beneteau (Oceanis), Jeanneau (Sun Odyssey), Bavaria, Dufour, Elan, Swan (smaller) |
| Large | 14-18m (46-59 ft) | Swan, Amel, X-Yachts, Grand Soleil, Contest, Najad |

**Total target**: ~12-15 yachts for initial MVP

### Scraping Approach

1. **Identify source websites**:
   - Manufacturer spec pages (most reliable)
   - Sailing magazine reviews (Sail Magazine, Yachting World)
   - Wikipedia boat lists (structured tables)

2. **Scraping tool**:
   - Use Puppeteer/Playwright (Node.js) to render JS-heavy pages
   - Use Cheerio/Basic fetch for static HTML
   - Respect robots.txt and rate limits (1 req/sec delay)

3. **Data normalization**:
   - Convert all measurements to metric (meters, kg, m²) if in imperial
   - Map manufacturer spec fields to our spec_categories (create categories on the fly)
   - Extract: core fields (length, beam, draft, displacement) + all other spec tables
   - Capture images (URL + alt text)
   - Store source URL and attribution

4. **Automated category discovery**:
   - Scraper scans all spec tables on a page
   - For each spec row, standardizes the label (e.g., "Length Overall" → "LOA", or we store the display label)
   - Suggests new spec category if label not found in spec_categories table
   - Human review step before seed: confirm category mappings

5. **Output**: JSONL or SQL inserts ready for seeding script

### Scraping Script Structure

```javascript
// scraper/yacht-scraper.js
- visit target manufacturer page (e.g., beneteau.com/oceanis-46)
- extract model name, year, all spec table rows
- normalize values (units conversion, type detection)
- map to spec category IDs (create new ones if missing)
- output structured record:
  {
    manufacturer: "Beneteau",
    model: "Oceanis 46",
    year: 2024,
    core: { length_overall: 14.2, beam: 4.3, ... },
    specs: { "Water Capacity": 600, "PHRF": 120, ... },
    images: [{url, alt}],
    source_url: "..."
  }
```

6. **Review & seed**:
   - Run scraper for each target yacht
   - Manual review of generated JSON to fix mappings/errors
   - Import into DB via seed script (upsert manufacturers, yacht_models, spec_values, images)

